President Cyril Ramaphosa will deliver the State of the Nation Address this evening. Speaking outside Parliament yesterday, he said he sees an opportunity to build a South Africa that every citizen deserves. CAPE TOWN - Democratic Alliance (DA) Chief Whip John Steenhuisen has urged President Cyril Ramaphosa to lay down a clear road map on how the ANC plans to get South Africa's economy working again. Ramaphosa will deliver the State of the Nation Address at 7pm on Thursday evening, where he's expected to outline key policies and strategies on how to elevate the country's current economic state. READ: A guide to Sona 2019 road closures With the country battling high levels of unemployment, corruption and slow economic growth, Steenhuisen says the ANC needs to implement bold reforms to alleviate South Africa's woes. "The Ramaphoria has given way to 'Ramareality'....the economy needs a jumpstart. What the president needs to do today is unambiguously set out what his plans are." South Africa's economy declined by 3,2% in the first quarter of 2019 resulting in the biggest quarterly contraction in 10 years. "This silly skirmish over the Reserve Bank is unsettling investors...he needs to set out a clear direction. International investors, local investors, ratings agencies are all watching very closely this Sona."